HEADWORD: Surloin
<hw>Sur"loin`</hw> <pr>(s⟦ucir⟧r"loin`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>surlonge</ets>; <ets>sur</ets> upon + <ets>longe</ets> loin. See
<er>Sur-</er>, and <er>Loin</er>.]</ety> <def>A loin of beef, or the
upper part of the loin. See <er>Sirloin</er>, the more usual, but not
etymologically preferable, orthography.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>sirloin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surly</ent>⟦br⟧
